Job Title: Data Migration & Fabric Data Warehouse – Multiple Roles
Ad Text:
IM Systems (IMS) is a strategic innovation consultancy specialising in aligning technology, data, and people to unlock real business potential. 

We partner with many of Australia’s most recognised public and private organisations, providing both strategic direction and hands-on expertise across digital, data and AI initiatives. 

At IMS, we value individuality, encourage innovation, and invest deeply in our people. We offer flexible work arrangements and foster a culture built on excellence, curiosity, and collaboration. 

Our consultants bring expertise across a broad range of domains including Data Governance, Data Strategy, Enterprise & Solution Architecture, Document & Records Management, Master Data, Business Intelligence, Analytics, Data Migration, Data Warehousing, AI/ML, Big Data and Program Management. 

Current Opportunities – Multiple Roles (6+ Month Contracts & Permanent) 

We are expanding our pool of highly skilled data professionals. Over the coming months, we will be onboarding talent across several data migration and data warehouse projects. Engagement durations vary from 6 to 12 months, with some permanent roles available. 

We are seeking experienced professionals for the following: 

Program Management – experience running both large scale data migration engagements, and data warehouse implementation engagements. Working with a sizeable team plus multiple parties to achieve high quality outcomes on time and on budget. Experience with ERP and/or health systems an advantage. 

Data & Solution Architecture & Analysts – data practitioners experienced in one or more of the following: data modelling (Erwin); data mappings; data architecture; solution architecture; data security; metadata management; encryption. 

Data Engineering – data engineers with experience in one or more of the following: MS Fabric / Databricks; batch / near real-time / CDC; CI/CD pipelines.  

Data Analytics & BI – practitioners to define, design and build out dashboards and/ or web applications. Skill sets needed include technical / data analysts; Power BI; AI / ML; Copilot. 

Data Governance – experience with data catalogues for glossaries, data lineage, data quality; establishing and populating templates (automated scanning). Experience in one or more of the following Purview; Informatica IDMC; Quest DI.

What We’re Looking For 

3+ years’ experience through to 10+ years as seasoned practitioners or leaders 

Eligibility to work in Australia 

Hybrid working model: 2–5 days per week onsite in Melbourne CBD 

Relevant qualifications and certifications valued 

Strong communication skills—both written and verbal 

High attention to detail and commitment to quality 

Ability to translate business needs into clear technical and functional documentation 

Collaborative approach, with the ability to work effectively across business, data and technical teams 

If you’re a confident, client-focused professional who thrives both independently and within team environments, we’d love to review your resume.  

Prior applicants are welcome to reapply. 


No agencies please.

Company Description


Turner & Townsend is a global professional services company with over 22,000 people in more than 62 countries.

Working with our clients across real estate, infrastructure, energy and natural resources, we transform together delivering outcomes that improve people’s lives. Working in partnership makes it possible to deliver the world’s most impactful projects and programmes as we turn challenge into opportunity and complexity into success.

Our capabilities include programme, project, cost, asset and commercial management, controls and performance, procurement and supply chain, net zero and digital solutions.

We are majority-owned by CBRE Group, Inc., the world’s largest commercial real estate services and investment firm, with our partners holding a significant minority interest. Turner & Townsend and CBRE work together to provide clients with the premier programme, project and cost management offering in markets around the world.

Please visit our website: www.turnerandtownsend.com

Job Description


We are seeking an exceptional Associate Director to drive growth in the market, lead strategic client relationships, and help us achieve our ambitious growth targets over the coming years. Due to increasing demand for our Infrastructure Digital – Data and Analytics services, this role will play a critical part in expanding our capabilities and delivering data excellence across our team and client engagements. We are looking for a commercially and technically minded leader with a proven track record of delivering successful data-driven solutions. The ideal candidate will be skilled in managing relationships and providing technical guidance across a multidisciplinary team spanning data visualisation, automation, infrastructure, data science, and systems implementation.

The Role

As the Associate Director, your responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Leverage a strong technical background to effectively engage with both clients and technical teams.
Lead client engagements, define delivery strategies, and provide technical assurance across complex data and analytics projects.
Manage and deliver system deployments across critical PMO functions, including cost control, schedule management, and risk mitigation.
Design, develop, and implement data-driven solutions in collaboration with clients and internal teams to generate actionable insights and enhance performance.
Produce comprehensive design documentation and technical specifications, including functional and non-functional requirements and end-to-end data processes.
Lead and contribute to business development initiatives, including the preparation of proposals and client presentations.
Cultivate new client relationships while maintaining and strengthening existing partnerships.
Oversee the development and deployment of data systems and pipelines, ensuring data quality and resolving any related issues.
Collaborate effectively within multidisciplinary teams to deliver integrated solutions.
Create high-quality communications, reports, and presentations tailored to diverse audiences.
Champion innovation and growth by mentoring team members and fostering an inclusive, high-performance culture.
Contribute to the development and continuous improvement of internal documentation, processes, and knowledge-sharing practices.

Qualifications


Essential Skills:

Proven experience implementing data reporting and dashboarding solutions
Experience with Agile delivery methodologies
Hands-on experience designing or implementing data architecture, particularly within the Azure data stack
Proficiency in analytics languages such as SQL or Python
A strong understanding of Project and Program management tools e.g. EcoSys/Contruent/Planview/Planisware/ InEIght/ Oracle Aconex/ Unifier
Exceptional communication skills – able to translate complex technical concepts for diverse audiences

Desirable Skills:

Experience with unit testing, integration testing, system testing, and user acceptance testing
Familiarity with data science approaches and best practices
Experience translating Azure data solution designs into actionable implementations
Background in requirements gathering, solution design, and implementation of data platforms
Experience working in multi-disciplinary teams (e.g., software engineers, DevOps, infrastructure, data scientists)
Exposure to Digital Twin, BIM and Internet of Things (IoT) solutions

System Knowledge:

Business Intelligence
Power BI / Tableau or similar 
 
Programming
Python / R Data or similar 
MS Visual Studio or similar 
MS365 Power Platform 
 
Database Platform Development
EcoSys / Contruent / Planview / Planisware / InEIght / Oracle Aconex / Unifier
Microsoft SQL + SSMS 
Microsoft Azure Platform (Synapse, Machine Learning, Databricks)

Additional Information


Our inspired people share our vision and mission. We provide a great place to work, where each person has the opportunity and voice to affect change.

We want our people to succeed both in work and life. To support this we promote a healthy, productive and flexible working environment that respects work-life balance. 

Turner & Townsend is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees and actively encourage applications from all sectors of the community.

Please find out more about us at www.turnerandtownsend.com/

Ad Text:
Senior Analyst - Simulation Delivery

Permanent full-time role within the ISP - Value Chain Performance (VCP)

Perth based role - Central Park

A work environment where safety is always the number one priority

We encourage women and Indigenous Peoples to apply, as we advance our business to more accurately reflect the world around us.


Where we're all welcome 

We are committed to an inclusive environment where people feel comfortable to be themselves. We want our people to feel that all voices are heard, all cultures respected and that a variety of perspectives are not only welcome - they are essential to our success. We treat each other fairly and with dignity regardless of race, gender, nationality, ethnic origin, religion, age, sexual orientation or anything else that makes us who we are. 

At Rio Tinto, we particularly welcome and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, women, the LGBTI+ community, mature workers, people with disabilities and people from different cultural backgrounds. 

We acknowledge that all people are different and believe that our differences are our strength.  The diversity of skills, life experiences and perspectives within our team enhances our way of working and our ability to achieve success together.    

About the role

We are seeking a Senior Analyst - Simulation Delivery to join our ISP - Value Chain Performance (VCP) division.

This role offers an exciting opportunity to make a tangible impact on how we plan and operate across the entire Rio Tinto Iron Ore (RTIO) supply chain.

As part of our Simulation Modelling team, you will play a critical role in delivering data-driven insights that support strategic decision-making. This position provides exposure to discrete event simulation tools and the chance to develop a holistic understanding of our end-to-end supply chain - from pit to port.

You will work closely with diverse teams across RTIO, collaborating with stakeholders at all levels to drive optimisation and influence key business outcomes.

Reporting to the Principal Simulation Delivery, you'll be at the heart of turning complex data into actionable insights that shape strategic decisions.

Your work will span across analytics, simulation, and stakeholder engagement, giving you a unique opportunity to influence how our supply chain operates. Key aspects of the role include:

Data Analytics & Insights - Collect, process, and analyse large operational datasets to create model inputs, validate results, and uncover insights that drive decision-making.

Simulation Experimentation - Design and run simulation experiments to answer critical business questions using scenario analysis and sensitivity testing.

Model Validation & Assurance - Ensure models accurately reflect real-world performance through rigorous validation and calibration.

Problem Framing - Define and structure analytical problems, selecting the right approach to deliver robust solutions.

Supply Chain Systems Understanding - Analyse interactions across mines, rail, and port systems to identify bottlenecks and optimisation opportunities.

Communication & Storytelling - Translate complex findings into clear, compelling narratives and visualisations that enable confident decisions.

Stakeholder Engagement - Build strong relationships with stakeholders, ensuring alignment, transparency, and successful delivery.

What you'll bring

A commitment to the safety of yourself and your team

Positive attitude with a willingness to make a difference

We're looking for a motivated and curious professional who enjoys solving complex problems and working collaboratively. Ideally, you'll have experience in the following areas:

Data Analysis - Strong analytical skills with proficiency in Python (highly desirable) or other analytical tools.

Problem Framing - Ability to define problems clearly and structure analytical approaches effectively.

Simulation Analysis - Experience setting up simulation experiments and interpreting results (preferred but not essential).

Supply Chain Knowledge - Understanding of the integrated mining supply chain, including how mines, rail, and port operations interact.

Communication - Skilled at translating complex analyses into clear, actionable insights for decision-making.

Stakeholder Engagement - Ability to build collaborative relationships and manage delivery outcomes effectively.

A C Class Manual drivers' licence

Note: Prior simulation modelling experience is advantageous but not mandatory.

If you are excited about the role and think you have what it takes but your experience doesn't align 100% we still want to hear from you. 

What we offer

Be recognised for your contribution, your thinking and your hard work, and go home knowing you've helped the world progress.

A work environment where safety is always the number one priority

A permanent position working directly for Rio Tinto

A competitive base salary reflective of your skills and experience with annual incentive program

Comprehensive medical benefits including subsidised private health insurance for employees and immediate family

Attractive share ownership plan

Company provided insurance cover

Extensive salary sacrifice & salary packaging options

Career development & education assistance to further your technical or leadership ambitions

Ongoing access to family-friendly health and medical wellbeing support

Leave for all of life's reasons (vacation/annual, paid parental, personal & cultural leave)

Exclusive employee discounts (banking, accommodation, cars, retail and more)

Possible domestic relocation assistance

We are committed to elevating Indigenous voices and increasing cultural knowledge in our business. Diversity of skills, life experiences and perspectives within our team enhances our way of working and our ability to achieve success together. To help you on your journey with us, you'll also have access to:

Specialist Indigenous Support Advisors are always there for our Indigenous employees and available to support through any aspect of your employment

Where you'll be working

You and your team will be Perth-based with opportunity to work flexibly from home combined with time in our Central Park offices. There will be the opportunity for some Pilbara site travel from time to time, however this will be performed on an ad-hoc basis.

In the Pilbara region of Western Australia, we own a world-class, integrated network of 17 mines, four independent port terminals, a rail network spanning nearly 2,000 kilometres and related infrastructure - all designed to respond rapidly to changes in demand. We are one of the world's leading producers and exporters of iron ore.

Our privately owned and operated rail network is an essential part of our integrated production process and services our 16 mines across the Pilbara via almost 2,000 km of track. With rail depots located at Tom Price, Cape Lambert and Dampier (7 Mile), most trains are autonomously operated and typically comprise three locomotives and 240 ore cars stretching to approximately 2.4 kilometres in length. We are also applying and adapting technology to improve safety and productivity across our rail network.

Who we are

Rio Tinto is a leading global mining and materials company. We operate in 35 countries where we produce iron ore, copper, aluminium, critical minerals and other materials needed for the global energy transition and for people, communities, and nations to thrive.

We have been mining for 150 years and operate with knowledge built up across generations and continents. Our purpose is finding better ways to provide the materials the world needs - striving for innovation and continuous improvement to produce materials with low emissions and to the right environmental, social and governance standards. But we can't do it on our own, so we're focused on creating partnerships to solve problems, create win-win and meet opportunities.

About Rio Tinto

Rio Tinto is a leading global mining and materials company. We operate in 35 countries where we produce iron ore, copper, aluminium, critical minerals, and other materials needed for the global energy transition and for people, communities, and nations to thrive.

We have been mining for 150 years and operate with knowledge built up across generations and continents. Our purpose is finding better ways to provide the materials the world needs - striving for innovation and continuous improvement to produce materials with low emissions and to the right environmental, social and governance standards. But we can't do it on our own, so we're focused on creating partnerships to solve problems, create win-win situations and meet opportunities.

We treat each other fairly and with dignity regardless of race, gender, nationality, ethnic origin, religion, age, sexual orientation or anything else that makes us different.

Job Title: Director Consulting Expert – Data And AI
Ad Text:
Position Description:


SUMMARY: 
Your future role and responsibilities:

. Lead enterprise-scale data and AI transformation programs, encompassing strategy, architecture, governance, and delivery.
. Advise C-suite and senior executives on leveraging data and AI to drive operational excellence, innovation, and new business models.
. Exceptional skills in Proposal development, SoW development and tender/bid responses.
. Develop and implement enterprise data strategies including data mesh, data fabric, governance, MDM, and ethical AI frameworks.
. Shape and deliver AI and ML initiatives, such as predictive analytics, generative AI adoption, automation, and intelligent decision support.
. Support business development by identifying opportunities to expand CGI's Data and AI footprint across industries.
. Create and present thought leadership—whitepapers, frameworks, and client briefings—on emerging trends such as generative AI, responsible AI, and data democratisation.
. Mentor and coach CGI consultants, developing future leaders in data science, analytics, and AI engineering.
. Collaborate across CGI's global network to align local delivery with global best practices in Data and AI innovation.
. Foster a culture of experimentation, curiosity, and continuous learning, promoting data literacy across the business.

Experience required to be successful in this role:

. Recognised as a leader in the field by alliance partners, including but not limited to AWS, Azure, Databricks, Snowflake and GCP.
. Proven experience leading enterprise data and AI transformation programs (e.g., data platform modernisation, AI/ML initiatives, analytics strategy).
. Strong understanding of data architecture, data engineering, governance, and cloud-based analytics platforms (AWS, Azure, Databricks, Snowflake and GCP).
. Expertise in AI technologies and frameworks (e.g., machine learning, NLP, computer vision, GenAI platforms).
. Demonstrated success advising senior executives and influencing strategic decision-making through data insights.
. Excellent business development and client relationship management skills, with a track record of growth in consulting engagements.
. Exceptional leadership, communication, and stakeholder management abilities.
. Relevant certifications in Data, AI, or Cloud.
. Experience with data ethics, AI governance, and regulatory compliance is advantageous, especially in regulated industries such as Financial Services.

What you can expect from us:


Together, as owners, let’s turn meaningful insights into action.

Life at CGI is rooted in ownership, teamwork, respect and belonging. Here, you’ll reach your full potential because…

You are invited to be an owner from day 1 as we work together to bring our Dream to life. That’s why we call ourselves CGI Partners rather than employees. We benefit from our collective success and actively shape our company’s strategy and direction.

Your work creates value. You’ll develop innovative solutions and build relationships with teammates and clients while accessing global capabilities to scale your ideas, embrace new opportunities, and benefit from expansive industry and technology expertise.

You’ll shape your career by joining a company built to grow and last. You’ll be supported by leaders who care about your health and well-being and provide you with opportunities to deepen your skills and broaden your horizons.

Come join our team—one of the largest IT and business consulting services firms in the world.
